The capital of Moldova is Chişinău. The local language is Romanian, but Russian is also widely spoken.[city]
Moldova is a multi-ethnic republic that has suffered under ethnic conflicts.
In 1994 this conflict led to the creation of the self-styled Transnistrian Republic in eastern Moldova, which has its own government and currency, but which is not recognised by any UN member state.
Economic relations have been restored between these two parts of Moldova, despite the breakdown in political negotiations.
The largest religion in Moldova is Orthodox Christianity.
